Warfare has a massive clarity issue. If planes are deployed where land units are, their icons overlap terribly. Without specifically going in to look at unit stacks in detail, you can't really tell what you're up against since a division can seemingly be literally any amount of anything. I still can't even work out how to split units up once they've merged. It's a very very tedious system.

Building speeds are still very odd. Building 1 of anything is just so fast it's crazy (e.g. if you want to fulfill the needs of Guyana, you can build just about everything you need in a day or two), but it then ironically flips into the opposite problem at scale where building lots of something is way too slow. For example I need 4Mn extra elementary seats in schools for Ethiopia. I can only build about 500-ish a year even with their fairly respectable build power speed, but that means I can barely chip away at the problem and fill about 400k seats a year (in a country with 110M+ population, it's a struggle to even keep up with the population growth). It would take 20+ years to deal with their secondary seats deficit with this system.

Not sure what a good solution would be to this, maybe letting us spend much more building power to build faster or something?
